h2.heading.heading--secondary#primary Primary button

p.paragraph.
  A call to action always has a meaningful text. An additional icon can be added.

.example
  .example__header
    .example__device-selection
      a.example__device-selection__device.example__device-selection__device--mobile
      a.example__device-selection__device.example__device-selection__device--tablet
      a.example__device-selection__device.example__device-selection__device--desktop.is-active
  .example__content.example__content--centered
      iframe.example__iframe
      .example__html(data-example-centered)
        .button Sample button
        !=' ' 
        .button
          svg.button__icon.button__icon--left.icon-svg
            use(xlink:href='/images/icons.svg#cross')
          | Icon and badge
          span.button__badge.badge 159
        !=' ' 
        .button
          | Icon right
          svg.button__icon.button__icon--right.icon-svg
            use(xlink:href='/images/icons.svg#cross')

.toggle
  .toggle__button(data-info, data-target='#code-1')
    svg.icon-svg.toggle__icon
      use(xlink:href='/images/icons.svg#source')
    span See code
  .toggle__content#code-1
    .tab-panel(data-tab, data-tab-default='html')
      .tab-panel__header
        .tab-panel__header__tabs
          .tab-panel__header__tab(data-tab-toggle='html') HTML
          .tab-panel__header__tab(data-tab-toggle='css') CSS
      .tab-panel__content
        .tab-panel__content__tab(data-tab-content='html')
          ul.checklist
            li.checklist__item.
              Prevent whitespace at the start and the end
              of the button. It will add some additional spacing 
              between the icon and the button.
            
          .tab-panel__content__tab__fullwidth-content
            .highlight: pre.highlight__listing.hljs: code.js
              :highlight
                <div class="button">Sample button</div>

                <div class="button"><svg class="button__icon button__icon--left icon-svg"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="/images/icons.svg#cross"></use></svg>Icon and badge<span class="button__badge badge">159</span></div>

                <div class="button">Icon right<svg class="button__icon button__icon--right icon-svg"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="/images/icons.svg#cross"></use></svg></div>

        .tab-panel__content__tab(data-tab-content='css')
          
          p.paragraph.
            Use the CSS classes mentioned in the HTML tab
            as mixins.

h3.heading.heading--tertiary UX Checklist

ul.checklist
  li.checklist__item
    There is always only one big primary call to action on any given page.

